genresAdvancedInfo.name: navajo
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre specifically refers to music created by members of the Navajo tribe, which incorporates traditional instruments such as the flute and drum. It often includes vocals in the Navajo language and draws on cultural and spiritual themes, such as the importance of harmony and balance in the natural world.
